  One hundred and seventeen new cases of Coronavirus have been recorded in Nigeria. According to a tweet from the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, (NCDC)  on Tuesday night, 59 cases were recorded in Lagos, 29 cases were discovered in the FCT, 14 cases were found out in Kano State and six cases were recorded in Borno State. The tweet further revealed that four cases were recorded in Katsina State, three in Ogun State and one in Rivers and Bauchi State This brings the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 782, with 25 deaths   Details Shortly…   